        <PARAL>\vd <rm>\compare\ 19.48cd: </rm>viśiṣṭhe tv{ }indriyagrāme tiryannarakasādhanam</PARAL>
        <NOTE>The phrase of Łtiryaṅnaraka$ appears in \MBH\ 3.181.18ab: 
                Łaśubhaiḥ karmabhiḥ pāpās tiryaṅnarakagāminaḥ$. Here <cite>GanguliMBh</cite> translates Łtiryaṅ$ 
                separately as `in a crooked way,' but I suspect that in the \VSS\ Łtiryannaraka$ has
                more to do with Łtiraggati$, being reduced to animal existence, being reborn as an animal or entering a 
                hell in animal form. 
                Cf. \MBH\ 13.134.057 (\verify):
                        Łnṛṣu janma labhante ye karmaṇā madhyamāḥ smṛtāḥ |
                        tiryaṅnarakagantāro hy adhamās te narādhamāḥ ||$,
                and ŁUmāmaheśvarasaṃvāda$ 6.1: 
                        Łavamanyanti ye viprān sarvaloke namaskṛtān |
                        narakaṃ yānti te sarve tiryagyoniṃ vrajanti ca ||$
                I suspect that Łnātirya°$ in the witnesses is only a scribal mistake for Łna tirya°$.</NOTE>
